[ AUG 85 CONTENTS: 
YOUNG, J. H85-198 ]

40
00:02:48,037 --> 00:02:50,263
I hope this is worth the two hour trip.

41
00:02:50,263 --> 00:02:51,801
I checked the H-records.

42
00:02:51,801 --> 00:02:55,297
There was a Joe Young, killed 1985.

43
00:02:55,297 --> 00:02:58,384
Well, this James Hogan, 
he's uh, dead guy's nephew?

44
00:02:58,384 --> 00:03:00,181
Heard something about the case.

45
00:03:00,181 --> 00:03:02,086
You two are pretty close, huh?

46
00:03:02,086 --> 00:03:03,155
Oh, close?

47
00:03:03,155 --> 00:03:05,689
I put him away for his 
grandma's murder last year.

48
00:03:05,689 --> 00:03:09,589
Yeah, but uh...
you got a soft spot for him.

49
00:03:09,987 --> 00:03:11,617
Why do you say that?

50
00:03:11,617 --> 00:03:13,676
Desk drawer full of love 
letters he's written you?

51
00:03:13,676 --> 00:03:15,735
They're not love letters.

52
00:03:16,051 --> 00:03:20,094
Just saying, maybe Jimbo roped you
out here to have himself a smile.

53
00:03:32,858 --> 00:03:34,727
How you making out, James?

54
00:03:34,727 --> 00:03:37,567
Didn't know you'd 
be bringing someone.

55
00:03:38,542 --> 00:03:39,944
My partner.

56
00:03:39,944 --> 00:03:41,554
Scotty Valens.

57
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:43,592
I could step out if 
you wanna be alone.

58
00:03:43,592 --> 00:03:45,859
Let's just get down to it.

59
00:03:48,102 --> 00:03:50,387
James?

60
00:03:50,387 --> 00:03:53,320
Uh...well, it's something 
I heard during counselling.

61
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:57,958
Guys admitting to the group, 
the lowest thing they've ever done.

62
00:03:58,393 --> 00:04:02,696
And uh...this older fella Ham Dun starts in, 
he says he's from the old neighborhood.

63
00:04:02,696 --> 00:04:03,893
Kensington.

64
00:04:03,893 --> 00:04:07,768
Back in '85 he says he came across 
a dead body at a local filling station.

65
00:04:07,768 --> 00:04:10,369
Which you realized was 
your uncle, Joe Young?

66
00:04:10,369 --> 00:04:14,299
Goes on to say, instead of reporting 
murder to the police he cleaned Joe out.

67
00:04:14,299 --> 00:04:16,435
Snaked away with twenty bucks.

68
00:04:16,435 --> 00:04:17,630
That's low, alright.

69
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:20,469
Back then, cops thought he 
was murdered in a petty stick-up.

70
00:04:20,469 --> 00:04:24,618
But you're hearing that he was already dead 
when Ham came by and took the dough.

71
00:04:24,618 --> 00:04:27,395
So the motive was 
something other than robbery.

72
00:04:27,395 --> 00:04:30,425
What you say about grabbing 
Ham out his cell, have a chat?

73
00:04:30,425 --> 00:04:32,396
He's not here.

74
00:04:32,396 --> 00:04:33,819
He got released.

75
00:04:33,819 --> 00:04:36,063
Last week.

76
00:04:37,929 --> 00:04:39,836
I'll find out where he went.

77
00:04:51,203 --> 00:04:53,315
So...

78
00:04:54,263 --> 00:04:55,811
How you getting along?

79
00:04:55,811 --> 00:04:59,143
Okay, I guess.

80
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:03,780
Have you been 
getting my letters?

81
00:05:03,780 --> 00:05:07,018
Yes, um...thank you.

82
00:05:07,488 --> 00:05:09,344
They didn't come 
off creepy, did they?

83
00:05:09,344 --> 00:05:12,013
No, no. They were...

84
00:05:12,459 --> 00:05:15,129
Nice, James.

85
00:05:15,129 --> 00:05:17,228
Sweet.

86
00:05:18,083 --> 00:05:21,719
Then why didn't 
you ever write back?

