550
00:29:24,515 --> 00:29:26,155
Told me what?

551
00:29:26,155 --> 00:29:28,479
Well, not in so many words but...

552
00:29:28,479 --> 00:29:30,974
Look, Joe I knew 
Johnstone was selling.

553
00:29:30,974 --> 00:29:33,261
In his office I saw the paper work.

554
00:29:33,261 --> 00:29:35,488
When?

555
00:29:35,488 --> 00:29:37,716
The day before 
he made his big speech.

556
00:29:37,716 --> 00:29:39,783
Saying Johnstone lied that day?

557
00:29:39,783 --> 00:29:42,201
To all of us guys?

558
00:29:42,201 --> 00:29:45,077
Without so much as a flinch.

559
00:29:48,616 --> 00:29:51,512
Think it's time for Plan B.

560
00:29:55,059 --> 00:29:57,443
He looked like someone 
had hit him in the gut.

561
00:29:57,443 --> 00:30:00,390
Becuase Johnstone 
had betrayed him?

562
00:30:00,390 --> 00:30:05,571
If Joe had one fault, it's that he trusted 
people when they gave their word.

563
00:30:05,571 --> 00:30:09,265
Never crossed his mind 
the boss man would lie.

564
00:30:09,890 --> 00:30:12,015
You know what Plan B was?

565
00:30:12,889 --> 00:30:14,614
Nah.

566
00:30:15,979 --> 00:30:18,582
I do.

567
00:30:22,196 --> 00:30:24,827
I got nothing to hide.

568
00:30:24,827 --> 00:30:27,866
Then let's talk about Plan B.

569
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:30,020
I don't know what that is.

570
00:30:30,020 --> 00:30:32,323
Butch, we know about the robbery.

571
00:30:32,323 --> 00:30:36,038
That you and Monty and Joe were 
planning to stick it to Johnstone.

572
00:30:37,250 --> 00:30:40,412
So maybe we talked about a plan.

573
00:30:40,548 --> 00:30:41,874
Guys can talk.

574
00:30:41,874 --> 00:30:44,072
We also checked 
police logs from '85.

575
00:30:44,072 --> 00:30:46,029
Joe's truck was seen in the area.

576
00:30:46,029 --> 00:30:47,904
Neighbor of Johnstone called it in.

577
00:30:47,904 --> 00:30:49,685
Two guys in a cab with him.

578
00:30:49,685 --> 00:30:52,054
Got a feeling one of'em was you.

579
00:30:52,054 --> 00:30:54,114
We get why you're lying.

580
00:30:54,378 --> 00:30:57,459
Admitting you did the robbery would 
put you with Joe at the night of the murder.

581
00:30:57,459 --> 00:31:01,412
But if that's all you did, 
a robbery 20 years ago.

582
00:31:01,412 --> 00:31:03,425
You don't have much to worry about.

583
00:31:03,425 --> 00:31:05,195
- No?
- No.

584
00:31:05,784 --> 00:31:08,476
But you gotta talk, Butch.

585
00:31:10,189 --> 00:31:13,464
Maybe we trespassed.

586
00:31:13,587 --> 00:31:14,880
Trespassed?

587
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:16,532
Nothing more.

588
00:31:18,449 --> 00:31:20,485
519 college.

589
00:31:20,719 --> 00:31:21,867
This is it.

590
00:31:21,867 --> 00:31:25,028
I know there's 
a Hi-Fi Pioneer turntable, receiver,

591
00:31:25,028 --> 00:31:26,915
speakers that gotta be worth a grand.

592
00:31:26,915 --> 00:31:28,823
That's two mortgage 
payments right there.

593
00:31:28,823 --> 00:31:31,660
I'll hit the bedroom, 
get whatever jewelry they've got.

594
00:31:34,847 --> 00:31:36,198
You said there was a china cabinet?

595
00:31:36,198 --> 00:31:38,124
First room on the left.

596
00:31:39,486 --> 00:31:42,016
Mary's never had 
a nice set of dishes.

597
00:31:43,299 --> 00:31:44,440
Oh, man...

598
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:45,901
- What?
- I don't know about this.

599
00:31:45,901 --> 00:31:49,946
Hey! Don't start pulling 
that crap, chicken man.

600
00:31:49,946 --> 00:31:51,686
It's unlocked.

601
00:31:54,774 --> 00:31:57,318
Ok, let's spread out.

602
00:32:01,634 --> 00:32:04,111
- Oh, no...
- What?

603
00:32:06,501 --> 00:32:08,843
He's gone.

604
00:32:09,482 --> 00:32:11,007
Son of a bitch!

605
00:32:11,007 --> 00:32:13,927
- Keep it down!
- Why?

606
00:32:14,036 --> 00:32:15,319
What's it matter now?

607
00:32:15,319 --> 00:32:16,865
He's right, Monty.

608
00:32:16,865 --> 00:32:19,935
Who the hell cares? 
There's not a thing here.

609
00:32:19,999 --> 00:32:25,234
Which makes me the biggest turkey in town 
because I believed everything he said!

610
00:32:25,234 --> 00:32:27,702
Damn it!

611
00:32:29,212 --> 00:32:30,257
Hey!

612
00:32:30,257 --> 00:32:32,307
That's gotta be worth something.

613
00:32:34,724 --> 00:32:36,587
- How do we get it down?- We'll pull it.

614
00:32:37,578 --> 00:32:39,660
Alright, boost me up.

615
00:32:59,118 --> 00:33:02,169
He promised he'd 
stay at Kensington.

616
00:33:02,169 --> 00:33:04,490
Promised to keep the mill open.

617
00:33:04,490 --> 00:33:07,699
Trying to steal a light fixture.

618
00:33:08,962 --> 00:33:11,644
It's pitiful.

619
00:33:15,331 --> 00:33:18,449
Monty and me went off drinking.

620
00:33:18,676 --> 00:33:21,320
That's the last
we ever saw of joe.

621
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:23,726
And that's your story?

622
00:33:23,844 --> 00:33:25,130
Yeah.

623
00:33:25,130 --> 00:33:27,490
Then Monty will
say the same thing?

624
00:33:27,490 --> 00:33:29,557
To the letter.

625
00:33:32,571 --> 00:33:33,815
Monty's wife called.

626
00:33:33,815 --> 00:33:37,360
She found a note from 
him on their kitchen table.

627
00:33:37,360 --> 00:33:40,820
Said he was going off to die.

628
00:33:41,526 --> 00:33:43,771
Not exactly a road map.

629
00:33:44,126 --> 00:33:47,417
Where does a guy 
like Monty go to end it?

630
00:33:48,301 --> 00:33:50,826
Live and die in the mills.

631
00:33:51,122 --> 00:33:51,992
What was that?

632
00:33:51,992 --> 00:33:56,606
When I was on the phone with 
James that's what Monty said he'd do.

633
00:34:20,840 --> 00:34:23,408
Easy does it there, Monty.

634
00:34:24,001 --> 00:34:26,128
I'm not doing nothing.

635
00:34:26,128 --> 00:34:28,836
Show us what you 
got in your hands.

636
00:34:31,561 --> 00:34:34,176
Double edge serrated blade?

637
00:34:34,342 --> 00:34:36,725
Guess we found our murder weapon.

638
00:34:36,725 --> 00:34:38,709
Wanna dry shave, son?

639
00:34:38,709 --> 00:34:41,200
Come on! Stay with us, Monty!

640
00:34:41,941 --> 00:34:43,470
I'm with ya.

641
00:34:43,956 --> 00:34:46,961
Just something we 
used to say to each other.

642
00:34:47,298 --> 00:34:49,278
goofing around.

643
00:34:49,278 --> 00:34:52,309
Who? You and Joe?

644
00:34:55,588 --> 00:34:57,946
What do you say we talk about him?

645
00:34:59,694 --> 00:35:02,007
Last thing I wanna do.

646
00:35:02,007 --> 00:35:04,257
So let's talk about Butch.

647
00:35:04,603 --> 00:35:08,532
All these years... 
you're still tight.

648
00:35:08,532 --> 00:35:11,081
- Not really.
- No?

649
00:35:11,543 --> 00:35:13,257
Why is that?

650
00:35:14,515 --> 00:35:16,910
He's a ghost.

651
00:35:16,910 --> 00:35:19,566
Reminder from my past.

652
00:35:20,037 --> 00:35:22,794
Just like this place is.

653
00:35:24,039 --> 00:35:28,599
Must've fixed this very loom 
say, dozen times.

654
00:35:28,599 --> 00:35:30,816
You were hard working.

655
00:35:30,816 --> 00:35:32,206
I respect that.

656
00:35:32,206 --> 00:35:34,065
I was tedious more than anything.

657
00:35:34,065 --> 00:35:36,867
More so for the guy
who has dreams.

658
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,985
Yeah, everybody says,
have 'em, but, uh,

659
00:35:39,985 --> 00:35:43,778
But uh, when they don't pan up,

660
00:35:43,778 --> 00:35:46,594
that's a whole other story, right?

661
00:35:46,666 --> 00:35:50,690
Pretty sure having 
dreams is my curse.

662
00:35:50,995 --> 00:35:54,172
See, I could fix a loom.

663
00:35:54,172 --> 00:35:56,984
Weave as well as weavers.

664
00:35:58,265 --> 00:36:00,833
It was a good life.

665
00:36:01,781 --> 00:36:04,914
For all of us.

666
00:36:13,935 --> 00:36:17,113
Wish I could've been like Joe.

667
00:36:17,809 --> 00:36:20,001
He was content.

668
00:36:20,001 --> 00:36:22,904
- But you weren't.
- No.

669
00:36:22,904 --> 00:36:25,432
You know Joe told me 
that was a good thing.

670
00:36:25,432 --> 00:36:27,791
He said dreaming up stuff, 
that was my gift.

671
00:36:27,791 --> 00:36:31,456
But you put a dreamer and 
a chicken in a same body and

672
00:36:31,456 --> 00:36:33,593
mister, you've got problems.

673
00:36:33,593 --> 00:36:35,399
No, Monty!

674
00:36:37,654 --> 00:36:39,441
Don't take the easy way.

675
00:36:39,441 --> 00:36:41,332
No! It's the perfect way!

676
00:36:41,332 --> 00:36:43,757
I have been a bawking chicken
my whole life.

677
00:36:43,757 --> 00:36:45,659
Than do it!

678
00:36:45,659 --> 00:36:47,802
I wanna see.

679
00:36:48,827 --> 00:36:52,946
No more. 
I wanna witness it.

680
00:36:53,406 --> 00:36:55,179
You wanna watch me kill myself?

681
00:36:55,179 --> 00:36:57,190
No joke, Monty. I wanna see.

682
00:36:57,190 --> 00:37:00,159
That, last step.

